criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Age >=15 years;

          -  More than one mediastinal lesions with diameter >= 1cm was detected by thoracic CT;

          -  Indication of biopsy to identify the etiology, including recently discovered
             mediastinal lesions or combination of clinical respiratory symptoms and complicated
             lung lesions implicated by thoracic image ;

          -  Completion of necessary preoperative laboratory examination;

          -  Informed consent form achievement.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Contradictions to bronchoscopy examination including severe cardio-pulmonary diseases,
             coagulation disorders, intolerance to asthenia, etc.;

          -  Failure to detect the lesions in ultrasonic landscape within 20 minutes;

          -  Indications of high risks to continue the biopsy such as abundant blood flow or
             adjacent large vessels detected by ultrasonic landscape.

          -  Psychiatric disorders or severe neurosis.

          -  Participation in other clinical experiments in recent 3 months;

          -  Any other conditions considered to be inappropriate to be involved in this study.
